  <exercise label="VARS_a5">
    <statement>
      <p>Fix the code below so that assigns <c>a</c> its correct value of <c>'a'</c>. Hint: use
        character operations!</p>
    </statement>
    <program interactive="activecode"
             line-numbers="yes"
             xml:id="VARS_a5q_editor">
      <input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    char a = 's';

    // Fix the line below.  Do NOT change the numbers!  Instead,
    // change the location of the parentheses.
    a = a - 3 * 4 + (1 + 3);

    // DO NOT MODIFY ANYTHING BELOW THIS LINE.
    cout << a;
}
        ]]></input>
    </program>
    <solution component="ex_solution"> Below is one way to complete the program. There are many
      creative ways that you could use the order of operations to come up with a complex expression
      that will bring you to 'a', here is one way. <program xml:id="VARS_a5a_editor"
               line-numbers="yes"><input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    char a = 's';
    a = a - (3 * (4 + 1) + 3);
    cout << a;
}
        ]]></input>
    </program>
    </solution>
  </exercise>

